author: @NoOne-sy5fg
text: DRY actually makes your code very efficient and easy to write, for example, one day I was making a function which for one very important reason had to be both static and non static, so what I did instead of copying the same method again was that, first I made the static method and then I'm the non static one (it had one parameter as the same class the method was in), so what I did was staticFunction(this); and that was literally it....
